  "title": "Tapping for fear of the night",
  "subtitle": "A five-minute script for releasing the association between darkness and dread.",
  "excerpt": "A five-minute tapping practice from Day 12 of the SLEEP program. The script targets the body's learned fear of bedtime: the flinch as evening draws in, the anticipation of a bad night before it has even started.",
  "type": "PRACTICE",
  "sourceNotes": "Adapted from Day 12 of SLEEP: A 30-Day Tapping Intensive to Fall Asleep Faster and Wake Energised (Rebecca J Page, 2025, ISBN 9798269649795), \"Release Fear of the Night.\" Tapping framework: Gary Craig's Emotional Freedom Technique (EFT), in use since the mid-1990s, building on Roger Callahan's Thought Field Therapy.",
